extendedInfo.description: Land Tycoon is a development and economic game where the player competes against 3 other players for control of a planet by buying and developing land plots which then generate resources that can be bought and sold on the planets commodities market.

reviews.title: Good Concept Poor execution.
reviews.comment: Three things that will make thus game better are.  1. Better markets. Markets need to fluctuate much more than they do. I got a message saying the price in iron dropped and it only dropped 2$? Should have dropped atleast 10. 2. Never ending game (bigger map) This game is much to short as is, and should continue until one person is left . Also a bigger map should go without saying.  3. Used/Produced bug fix In the info section it said I used 12 and produced 2 but I gained 11? Whats with that?  Still fun tho.
reviews.author: Mitchell Szukalow

reviews.title: Great start, could be epic with tweaks
reviews.comment: Great concept and decent exicution.  Needs bugs fixed, option for fast forward through other players, options for more interaction between opponents (buy sell trade), would like to know current resource requirements, a use for gold, a clear ending
reviews.author: David Howard

reviews.title: Painfully Hilarious
reviews.comment: This game is hilarious; its economy is so poorly designed that the AI go bankrupt every game. There is little real chance to the game, since all of the events are counter-reactive to the players actions with the intent of screwing you; but, that just makes them predictable and easy to manipulate. I talked to the devs about all of this and the dongs just made a bunch of excuses ...they don\'t know what they are doing.
